Anna M. H. Wit, Appellant, v. State of New York, Respondent. (Claim No. 37168.) Submitted February 17, 1964; decided February 20, 1964. Louis J. Lefkowitz, Attorney-General (Harold J. Hughes, Jr., of counsel), for motion. (See 19 A D 2d 941.)

No one opposed.

Motion granted and appeal dismissed, with costs and $10 costs of motion, upon the ground that the order sought to be appealed from does not finally determine the action within the meaning of the Constitution.
